This challenge is tricky as the decompiled code is difficult to understand at first. Let's dive in and run the challenge:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

We could try to use strings:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Nothing here, so we now run the mighty Ghidra and take a look at the decompiled C code:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

We need a 10 characters long guess. Let's analyse the others functions.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Content of the values to shift:

| Hex |     | Bin            |     | Dec |
| --- | --- | -------------- | --- | --- |
| 200 |     | 0010 0000 0000 |     | 512 |
| 8   |     | 0000 0000 1000 |     | 8   |
| 80  |     | 0000 1000 0000 |     | 128 |
| 1   |     | 0000 0000 0001 |     | 1   |
| 400 |     | 0100 0000 0000 |     |     |

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Content of the results to get:

| Hex |     | Bin            |     | Dec |
| --- | --- | -------------- | --- | --- |
| 40  |     | 0000 0100 0000 |     | 64  |
| 100 |     | 0001 0000 0000 |     | 256 |
| 200 |     | 0010 0000 0000 |     | 542 |
| 40  |     | 0000 0100 0000 |     | 64  |
| 2   |     | 0000 0000 0010 |     | 2   |

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The first param represent the adress of our guess, and param_2 is the offset (multiplied by 2).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

It looks like guess has to contains only numerical characters, from '0' to '9'. It then converts the character in an integer (similar to the function atoi). We quickly verify it with a python line:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

We successfully converted the character '1' into the number 1.

To sum up, each even character (starting at 0) of our guess has to be a direction: 'L' or 'R', and the odd characters represent the number of shifts (the << or >> operator), from 0 to 9. We now dress the table of the lock positions and good associated combination to guess the direction and number of shifts needed to get in the good configuration.

For exemple, the lock 0010 must shit to the left 2 times to reach the combination 1000. Let's try with the challenge values:

| Lock           |     | Combination    | Dir | Shifts |
| -------------- | --- | -------------- | --- | ------ |
| 0010 0000 0000 | \-> | 0000 0100 0000 | R   | 3      |
| 0000 0000 1000 | \-> | 0001 0000 0000 | L   | 5      |
| 0000 1000 0000 | \-> | 0010 0000 0000 | L   | 2      |
| 0000 0000 0001 | \-> | 0000 0100 0000 | L   | 6      |
| 0100 0000 0000 | \-> | 0000 0000 0010 | R   | 9      |

The flag should be : R3L5L2L6R9.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Well done!
